news.title: Chandigarh housing board to end tatkal scheme, quick services a click away
news.para: Sources said the board has submitted a proposal to UT adviser Dharam Pal, who is also the CHB chairman, that it has started providing online timely and speedy services therefore the tatkal facility was no longer required.

news.title: Ludhiana: Regularisation fee pending? Builders to be booked
news.para: Before purchasing any plot in the city, the residents have been advised to visit the MC website and check whether the colony is legal or not. The civic officials have uploaded the list of all colonies on the MC website.

news.title: Gurugram: Three illegal colonies razed, 12 acres freed in Bhondsi & Naya Gaon
news.para: Around 100 structures, including 15 under construction houses, shops and boundary walls were demolished, an official said. in the presence of police during the drive.
